citations.narrative:
Three outdoor runs have areas of wire points on the bottom part of the panel that the dogs could possibly contact. Wire
points could be sharp and injure dogs. To prevent injury, ensure that panels are free from points that dogs could contact.
***Correct by 12/16/2023.

The facility has had regular scheduled visits by the attending veterinarian (AV), however the yearly adult physical exams
are about one and a half months overdue. The licensee has been in communication with the AV's clinic to see when it can
be done. Routine physical exams within every 12 months are required and help ensure dogs are healthy. Ensure that the
adult physical exams by the AV get scheduled and completed.
***Correct by 1/14/2024.
This inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives.
